Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 6:52 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of December 31, 2015, Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund has gone out of business. Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Nile Capital Management, LLC. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of frontier market countries across the world. The fund invests directly and through other funds in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. For its equity portion, it primarily invests in value and growth stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. For its fixed-income portion, the fund invests in fixed income securities including bills, notes, ...
As of December 31, 2015, Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund has gone out of business. Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Nile Capital Management, LLC. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of frontier market countries across the world. The fund invests directly and through other funds in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. For its equity portion, it primarily invests in value and growth stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. For its fixed-income portion, the fund invests in fixed income securities including bills, notes, bonds, senior loans, participation notes, pass-through certificates, asset-backed securities, mortgage-backed securities, and certificates of deposit issued by or guaranteed by companies, governments, their agencies and instrumentalities, and multi-national organizations. It invests in securities across all credit ratings and maturities. The fund employs fundamental analysis with both top-down and bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors such as outlook for economic growth, inflation, interest rates, currency, regulatory framework, political stability, cash flow return on investments, returns on invested capital, health of balance sheets, strong competitive advantages, prospects for earnings growth, strength of management, sound financial management, sound accounting policies, pricing flexibility, attractiveness of each investment opportunity, general market, political and economic conditions, and expected future returns of investments to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the MSCI Frontier Markets Index (Net TR). The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. It was formerly known as Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Global Frontier Fund. Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Frontier and Emerging Fund was formed on December 31, 2013 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


116 Village BoulevardSuite 306Princeton, NJ 08540United StatesFounded in 2013



Phone: 646-367-2820

Fax: 646-367-2815








