Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Africa, Frontier and Emerging Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 6:52 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Africa, Frontier and Emerging Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Africa, Frontier and Emerging Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Nile Capital Management, LLC. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of African, frontier and emerging countries across the globe. For its equity portion, the fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in growth and value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. For the fixed-income portion, the fund invests in fixed income securities including bills, notes, bonds, senior loans, participation notes, pass-through certificates, asset-backed securities, mortgage-backed securities, and certifica...
Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Africa, Frontier and Emerging Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Nile Capital Management, LLC. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of African, frontier and emerging countries across the globe. For its equity portion, the fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in growth and value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. For the fixed-income portion, the fund invests in fixed income securities including bills, notes, bonds, senior loans, participation notes, pass-through certificates, asset-backed securities, mortgage-backed securities, and certificates of deposit issued by or guaranteed by companies, governments, their agencies and instrumentalities, and multi-national organizations. It invests in debt securities with varying maturity and credit quality. The fund employs fundamental analysis with a combination of top-down and bottom-up security selection approach, focusing on factors such as a country's outlook for economic growth, inflation, interest rates, currency, regulatory framework, political stability, the supply and demand trends for various industries, cash flow return on investments, returns on invested capital, health of balance sheets, strong competitive advantages, prospects for earnings growth, strength of management, sound financial management, sound accounting policies, pricing flexibility, attractiveness of each investment opportunity, general market, political and economic conditions, and expected future returns of investments to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the MSCI Frontier Markets Index Net TR and MSCI Emerging Markets Index. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. It was formerly known as Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Pan Africa Fund. Nile Capital Investment Trust - Nile Africa, Frontier and Emerging Fund was formed on April 28, 2010 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


116 Village BoulevardSuite 306Princeton, NJ 08540United StatesFounded in 2010



Phone: 646-367-2820

Fax: 646-367-2815

nilefunds.com/our-funds/







